{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"In 1962, with Rachel Carson's \"Silent Spring,\""},{"time":5000,"text":"I think for people like me in the world of the making of things,"},{"time":10000,"text":"the canary in the mine wasn't singing."},{"time":14000,"text":"And so the question that we might not have birds"},{"time":17000,"text":"became kind of fundamental to those of us wandering around"},{"time":20000,"text":"looking for the meadowlarks that seemed to have all disappeared."},{"time":23000,"text":"And the question was, were the birds singing?"},{"time":26000,"text":"Now, I'm not a scientist, that'll be really clear."},{"time":30000,"text":"But, you know, we've just come from this discussion of what a bird might be."},{"time":34000,"text":"What is a bird?"},{"time":35000,"text":"Well, in my world, this is a rubber duck."},{"time":39000,"text":"It comes in California with a warning --"},{"time":41000,"text":"\"This product contains chemicals known by the State of California"},{"time":44000,"text":"to cause cancer and birth defects or other reproductive harm.\""},{"time":51000,"text":"This is a bird."},{"time":54000,"text":"What kind of culture would produce a product of this kind"},{"time":57000,"text":"and then label it and sell it to children?"},{"time":62000,"text":"I think we have a design problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"Someone heard the six hours of talk that I gave"},{"time":70000,"text":"called \"The Monticello Dialogues\" on NPR, and sent me this as a thank you note --"},{"time":76000,"text":"\"We realize that design is a signal of intention,"},{"time":78000,"text":"but it also has to occur within a world,"},{"time":81000,"text":"and we have to understand that world in order to"},{"time":85000,"text":"imbue our designs with inherent intelligence,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and so as we look back at the basic state of affairs"},{"time":93000,"text":"in which we design, we, in a way, need to go to the primordial condition"},{"time":98000,"text":"to understand the operating system and the frame conditions of a planet,"},{"time":103000,"text":"and I think the exciting part of that is the good news that's there,"},{"time":108000,"text":"because the news is the news of abundance,"},{"time":111000,"text":"and not the news of limits,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and I think as our culture tortures itself now"},{"time":118000,"text":"with tyrannies and concerns over limits and fear,"},{"time":123000,"text":"we can add this other dimension of abundance that is coherent,"},{"time":128000,"text":"driven by the sun, and start to imagine"},{"time":130000,"text":"what that would be like to share.\""},{"time":137000,"text":"That was a nice thing to get."},{"time":139000,"text":"That was one sentence."},{"time":143000,"text":"Henry James would be proud."},{"time":145000,"text":"This is -- I put it down at the bottom,"},{"time":147000,"text":"but that was extemporaneous, obviously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"The fundamental issue is that, for me,"},{"time":153000,"text":"design is the first signal of human intentions."},{"time":155000,"text":"So what are our intentions, and what would our intentions be --"},{"time":159000,"text":"if we wake up in the morning, we have designs on the world --"},{"time":162000,"text":"well, what would our intention be as a species"},{"time":164000,"text":"now that we're the dominant species?"},{"time":166000,"text":"And it's not just stewardship and dominion debate,"},{"time":169000,"text":"because really, dominion is implicit in stewardship --"},{"time":175000,"text":"because how could you dominate something you had killed?"},{"time":177000,"text":"And stewardship's implicit in dominion,"},{"time":179000,"text":"because you can't be steward of something if you can't dominate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"So the question is, what is the first question for designers?"},{"time":187000,"text":"Now, as guardians -- let's say the state, for example,"},{"time":190000,"text":"which reserves the right to kill, the right to be duplicitous and so on --"},{"time":195000,"text":"the question we're asking the guardian at this point is"},{"time":198000,"text":"are we meant, how are we meant,"},{"time":200000,"text":"to secure local societies, create world peace"},{"time":202000,"text":"and save the environment?"},{"time":204000,"text":"But I don't know that that's the common debate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"Commerce, on the other hand, is relatively quick,"},{"time":211000,"text":"essentially creative, highly effective and efficient,"},{"time":213000,"text":"and fundamentally honest, because we can't exchange"},{"time":216000,"text":"value for very long if we don't trust each other."},{"time":220000,"text":"So we use the tools of commerce primarily for our work,"},{"time":222000,"text":"but the question we bring to it is,"},{"time":224000,"text":"how do we love all the children of all species for all time?"},{"time":228000,"text":"And so we start our designs with that question."},{"time":231000,"text":"Because what we realize today is that modern culture"},{"time":233000,"text":"appears to have adopted a strategy of tragedy."},{"time":236000,"text":"If we come here and say, \"Well, I didn't intend"},{"time":238000,"text":"to cause global warming on the way here,\""},{"time":239000,"text":"and we say, \"That's not part of my plan,\""},{"time":241000,"text":"then we realize it's part of our de facto plan."},{"time":244000,"text":"Because it's the thing that's happening because we have no other plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"And I was at the White House for President Bush,"},{"time":249000,"text":"meeting with every federal department and agency,"},{"time":251000,"text":"and I pointed out that they appear to have no plan."},{"time":255000,"text":"If the end game is global warming, they're doing great."},{"time":257000,"text":"If the end game is mercury toxification of our children"},{"time":260000,"text":"downwind of coal fire plants as they scuttled the Clean Air Act,"},{"time":263000,"text":"then I see that our education programs should be explicitly defined as,"},{"time":267000,"text":"\"Brain death for all children. No child left behind.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"So, the question is, how many federal officials"},{"time":277000,"text":"are ready to move to Ohio and Pennsylvania with their families?"},{"time":280000,"text":"So if you don't have an endgame of something delightful,"},{"time":284000,"text":"then you're just moving chess pieces around,"},{"time":286000,"text":"if you don't know you're taking the king."},{"time":287000,"text":"So perhaps we could develop a strategy of change,"},{"time":290000,"text":"which requires humility. And in my business as an architect,"},{"time":293000,"text":"it's unfortunate the word \"humility\" and the word \"architect\""},{"time":297000,"text":"have not appeared in the same paragraph since \"The Fountainhead.\""},{"time":300000,"text":"So if anybody here has trouble with the concept of design humility,"},{"time":305000,"text":"reflect on this -- it took us 5,000 years"},{"time":308000,"text":"to put wheels on our luggage."},{"time":312000,"text":"So, as Kevin Kelly pointed out, there is no endgame."},{"time":317000,"text":"There is an infinite game, and we're playing in that infinite game."},{"time":321000,"text":"And so we call it \"cradle to cradle,\""},{"time":323000,"text":"and our goal is very simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"This is what I presented to the White House."},{"time":326000,"text":"Our goal is a delightfully diverse, safe, healthy and just world,"},{"time":329000,"text":"with clean air, clean water, soil and power --"},{"time":332000,"text":"economically, equitably, ecologically and elegantly enjoyed, period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"What don't you like about this?"},{"time":342000,"text":"Which part of this don't you like?"},{"time":344000,"text":"So we realized we want full diversity,"},{"time":346000,"text":"even though it can be difficult to remember what De Gaulle said"},{"time":349000,"text":"when asked what it was like to be President of France."},{"time":351000,"text":"He said, \"What do you think it's like trying to run a country with 400 kinds of cheese?\""},{"time":355000,"text":"But at the same time, we realize that our products are not safe and healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"So we've designed products"},{"time":360000,"text":"and we analyzed chemicals down to the parts per million."},{"time":362000,"text":"This is a baby blanket by Pendleton that will give your child nutrition"},{"time":365000,"text":"instead of Alzheimer's later in life."},{"time":367000,"text":"We can ask ourselves, what is justice,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and is justice blind, or is justice blindness?"},{"time":373000,"text":"And at what point did that uniform turn from white to black?"},{"time":378000,"text":"Water has been declared a human right by the United Nations."},{"time":381000,"text":"Air quality is an obvious thing to anyone who breathes."},{"time":383000,"text":"Is there anybody here who doesn't breathe?"},{"time":386000,"text":"Clean soil is a critical problem -- the nitrification, the dead zones"},{"time":389000,"text":"in the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":391000,"text":"A fundamental issue that's not being addressed."},{"time":393000,"text":"We've seen the first form of solar energy"},{"time":395000,"text":"that's beat the hegemony of fossil fuels in the form of wind"},{"time":398000,"text":"here in the Great Plains, and so that hegemony is leaving."},{"time":401000,"text":"And if we remember Sheikh Yamani when he formed OPEC,"},{"time":404000,"text":"they asked him, \"When will we see the end of the age of oil?\""},{"time":407000,"text":"I don't know if you remember his answer, but it was,"},{"time":410000,"text":"\"The Stone Age didn't end because we ran out of stones.\""},{"time":414000,"text":"We see that companies acting ethically in this world"},{"time":418000,"text":"are outperforming those that don't."},{"time":419000,"text":"We see the flows of materials in a rather terrifying prospect."},{"time":424000,"text":"This is a hospital monitor from Los Angeles, sent to China."},{"time":427000,"text":"This woman will expose herself to toxic phosphorous,"},{"time":430000,"text":"release four pounds of toxic lead into her childrens' environment,"},{"time":433000,"text":"which is from copper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"On the other hand, we see great signs of hope."},{"time":437000,"text":"Here's Dr. Venkataswamy in India, who's figured out"},{"time":440000,"text":"how to do mass-produced health."},{"time":442000,"text":"He has given eyesight to two million people for free."},{"time":446000,"text":"We see in our material flows that car steels don't become car steel again"},{"time":449000,"text":"because of the contaminants of the coatings --"},{"time":451000,"text":"bismuth, antimony, copper and so on."},{"time":453000,"text":"They become building steel."},{"time":454000,"text":"On the other hand, we're working with Berkshire Hathaway,"},{"time":456000,"text":"Warren Buffett and Shaw Carpet,"},{"time":459000,"text":"the largest carpet company in the world."},{"time":460000,"text":"We've developed a carpet that is continuously recyclable,"},{"time":463000,"text":"down to the parts per million."},{"time":466000,"text":"The upper is Nylon 6 that can go back to caprolactam,"},{"time":469000,"text":"the bottom, a polyolephine -- infinitely recyclable thermoplastic."},{"time":472000,"text":"Now if I was a bird, the building on my left is a liability."},{"time":476000,"text":"The building on my right, which is our corporate campus for The Gap"},{"time":479000,"text":"with an ancient meadow, is an asset -- its nesting grounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Here's where I come from. I grew up in Hong Kong,"},{"time":486000,"text":"with six million people in 40 square miles."},{"time":488000,"text":"During the dry season, we had four hours of water every fourth day."},{"time":492000,"text":"And the relationship to landscape was that of farmers who have been"},{"time":495000,"text":"farming the same piece of ground for 40 centuries."},{"time":499000,"text":"You can't farm the same piece of ground for 40 centuries"},{"time":501000,"text":"without understanding nutrient flow."},{"time":504000,"text":"My childhood summers were in the Puget Sound of Washington,"},{"time":507000,"text":"among the first growth and big growth."},{"time":509000,"text":"My grandfather had been a lumberjack in the Olympics,"},{"time":511000,"text":"so I have a lot of tree karma I am working off."},{"time":516000,"text":"I went to Yale for graduate school,"},{"time":518000,"text":"studied in a building of this style by Le Corbusier,"},{"time":520000,"text":"affectionately known in our business as Brutalism."},{"time":524000,"text":"If we look at the world of architecture,"},{"time":527000,"text":"we see with Mies' 1928 tower for Berlin,"},{"time":530000,"text":"the question might be, \"Well, where's the sun?\""},{"time":532000,"text":"And this might have worked in Berlin, but we built it in Houston,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and the windows are all closed. And with most products"},{"time":538000,"text":"appearing not to have been designed for indoor use,"},{"time":540000,"text":"this is actually a vertical gas chamber."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543000,"text":"When I went to Yale, we had the first energy crisis,"},{"time":546000,"text":"and I was designing the first solar-heated house in Ireland"},{"time":548000,"text":"as a student, which I then built --"},{"time":550000,"text":"which would give you a sense of my ambition."},{"time":552000,"text":"And Richard Meier, who was one of my teachers,"},{"time":554000,"text":"kept coming over to my desk to give me criticism,"},{"time":556000,"text":"and he would say, \"Bill, you've got to understand- --"},{"time":558000,"text":"solar energy has nothing to do with architecture.\""},{"time":566000,"text":"I guess he didn't read Vitruvius."},{"time":568000,"text":"In 1984, we did the first so-called \"green office\" in America"},{"time":572000,"text":"for Environmental Defense."},{"time":573000,"text":"We started asking manufacturers what were in their materials."},{"time":576000,"text":"They said, \"They're proprietary, they're legal, go away.\""},{"time":578000,"text":"The only indoor quality work done in this country at that time"},{"time":580000,"text":"was sponsored by R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Company,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and it was to prove there was no danger"},{"time":584000,"text":"from secondhand smoke in the workplace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"So, all of a sudden, here I am, graduating from high school in 1969,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and this happens, and we realize that \"away\" went away."},{"time":594000,"text":"Remember we used to throw things away, and we'd point to away?"},{"time":598000,"text":"And yet, NOAA has now shown us, for example --"},{"time":600000,"text":"you see that little blue thing above Hawaii?"},{"time":602000,"text":"That's the Pacific Gyre."},{"time":603000,"text":"It was recently dragged for plankton by scientists,"},{"time":605000,"text":"and they found six times as much plastic as plankton."},{"time":609000,"text":"When asked, they said, \"It's kind of like a giant toilet that doesn't flush.\""},{"time":614000,"text":"Perhaps that's away."},{"time":615000,"text":"So we're looking for the design rules of this --"},{"time":617000,"text":"this is the highest biodiversity of trees in the world, Irian Jaya,"},{"time":619000,"text":"259 species of tree, and we described this"},{"time":623000,"text":"in the book, \"Cradle to Cradle.\""},{"time":624000,"text":"The book itself is a polymer. It is not a tree."},{"time":628000,"text":"That's the name of the first chapter -- \"This Book is Not a Tree.\""},{"time":631000,"text":"Because in poetics, as Margaret Atwood pointed out,"},{"time":634000,"text":"\"we write our history on the skin of fish"},{"time":636000,"text":"with the blood of bears.\""},{"time":639000,"text":"And with so much polymer, what we really need"},{"time":640000,"text":"is technical nutrition, and to use something"},{"time":643000,"text":"as elegant as a tree -- imagine this design assignment:"},{"time":646000,"text":"Design something that makes oxygen, sequesters carbon,"},{"time":648000,"text":"fixes nitrogen, distills water, accrues solar energy as fuel,"},{"time":652000,"text":"makes complex sugars and food, creates microclimates,"},{"time":656000,"text":"changes colors with the seasons and self-replicates."},{"time":662000,"text":"Well, why don't we knock that down and write on it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"So, we're looking at the same criteria"},{"time":672000,"text":"as most people -- you know, can I afford it?"},{"time":674000,"text":"Does it work? Do I like it?"},{"time":676000,"text":"We're adding the Jeffersonian agenda, and I come from Charlottesville,"},{"time":678000,"text":"where I've had the privilege of living in a house designed by Thomas Jefferson."},{"time":682000,"text":"We're adding life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness."},{"time":688000,"text":"Now if we look at the word \"competition,\""},{"time":689000,"text":"I'm sure most of you've used it."},{"time":691000,"text":"You know, most people don't realize it comes from"},{"time":692000,"text":"the Latin competere, which means strive together."},{"time":695000,"text":"It means the way Olympic athletes train with each other."},{"time":698000,"text":"They get fit together, and then they compete."},{"time":701000,"text":"The Williams sisters compete -- one wins Wimbledon."},{"time":703000,"text":"So we've been looking at the idea of competition"},{"time":706000,"text":"as a way of cooperating in order to get fit together."},{"time":710000,"text":"And the Chinese government has now --"},{"time":711000,"text":"I work with the Chinese government now --"},{"time":713000,"text":"has taken this up."},{"time":715000,"text":"We're also looking at survival of the fittest,"},{"time":717000,"text":"not in just competition terms in our modern context"},{"time":719000,"text":"of destroy the other or beat them to the ground,"},{"time":722000,"text":"but really to fit together and build niches"},{"time":724000,"text":"and have growth that is good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"Now most environmentalists don't say growth is good,"},{"time":728000,"text":"because, in our lexicon, asphalt is two words: assigning blame."},{"time":733000,"text":"But if we look at asphalt as our growth,"},{"time":736000,"text":"then we realize that all we're doing is destroying"},{"time":738000,"text":"the planetary's fundamental underlying operating system."},{"time":742000,"text":"So when we see E equals mc squared come along, from a poet's perspective,"},{"time":747000,"text":"we see energy as physics, chemistry as mass,"},{"time":749000,"text":"and all of a sudden, you get this biology."},{"time":751000,"text":"And we have plenty of energy, so we'll solve that problem,"},{"time":754000,"text":"but the biology problem's tricky, because as we put through"},{"time":757000,"text":"all these toxic materials that we disgorge,"},{"time":760000,"text":"we will never be able to recover that."},{"time":762000,"text":"And as Francis Crick pointed out, nine years"},{"time":764000,"text":"after discovering DNA with Mr. Watson,"},{"time":767000,"text":"that life itself has to have growth as a precondition --"},{"time":771000,"text":"it has to have free energy, sunlight"},{"time":773000,"text":"and it needs to be an open system of chemicals."},{"time":776000,"text":"So we're asking for human artifice to become a living thing,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and we want growth, we want free energy from sunlight"},{"time":781000,"text":"and we want an open metabolism for chemicals."},{"time":784000,"text":"Then, the question becomes not growth or no growth,"},{"time":786000,"text":"but what do you want to grow?"},{"time":789000,"text":"So instead of just growing destruction,"},{"time":791000,"text":"we want to grow the things that we might enjoy,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and someday the FDA will allow us to make French cheese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796000,"text":"So therefore, we have these two metabolisms,"},{"time":800000,"text":"and I worked with a German chemist, Michael Braungart,"},{"time":802000,"text":"and we've identified the two fundamental metabolisms."},{"time":804000,"text":"The biological one I'm sure you understand,"},{"time":806000,"text":"but also the technical one, where we take materials"},{"time":808000,"text":"and put them into closed cycles."},{"time":810000,"text":"We call them biological nutrition and technical nutrition."},{"time":813000,"text":"Technical nutrition will be in an order of magnitude of biological nutrition."},{"time":817000,"text":"Biological nutrition can supply about 500 million humans,"},{"time":820000,"text":"which means that if we all wore Birkenstocks and cotton,"},{"time":822000,"text":"the world would run out of cork and dry up."},{"time":825000,"text":"So we need materials in closed cycles,"},{"time":827000,"text":"but we need to analyze them down to the parts per million"},{"time":829000,"text":"for cancer, birth defects, mutagenic effects,"},{"time":832000,"text":"disruption of our immune systems, biodegradation, persistence,"},{"time":835000,"text":"heavy metal content, knowledge of how we're making them"},{"time":838000,"text":"and their production and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"Our first product was a textile where we analyzed 8,000 chemicals"},{"time":844000,"text":"in the textile industry."},{"time":845000,"text":"Using those intellectual filters, we eliminated [7,962.]"},{"time":850000,"text":"We were left with 38 chemicals."},{"time":852000,"text":"We have since databased the 4000 most commonly used chemicals"},{"time":855000,"text":"in human manufacturing, and we're releasing this database into the public in six weeks."},{"time":860000,"text":"So designers all over the world can analyze their products"},{"time":862000,"text":"down to the parts per million for human and ecological health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"We've developed a protocol so that companies can send"},{"time":875000,"text":"these same messages all the way through their supply chains,"},{"time":878000,"text":"because when we asked most companies we work with -- about a trillion dollars"},{"time":881000,"text":"-- and say, \"Where does your stuff come from?\" They say, \"Suppliers.\""},{"time":883000,"text":"\"And where does it go?\""},{"time":885000,"text":"\"Customers.\""},{"time":886000,"text":"So we need some help there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"So the biological nutrients, the first fabrics --"},{"time":889000,"text":"the water coming out was clean enough to drink."},{"time":891000,"text":"Technical nutrients -- this is for Shaw Carpet, infinitely reusable carpet."},{"time":895000,"text":"Here's nylon going back to caprolactam back to carpet."},{"time":898000,"text":"Biotechnical nutrients -- the Model U for Ford Motor,"},{"time":901000,"text":"a cradle to cradle car -- concept car."},{"time":903000,"text":"Shoes for Nike, where the uppers are polyesters, infinitely recyclable,"},{"time":907000,"text":"the bottoms are biodegradable soles."},{"time":910000,"text":"Wear your old shoes in, your new shoes out."},{"time":912000,"text":"There is no finish line."},{"time":914000,"text":"The idea here of the car is that some of the materials"},{"time":916000,"text":"go back to the industry forever, some of the materials go back to soil --"},{"time":919000,"text":"it's all solar-powered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"Here's a building at Oberlin College we designed"},{"time":923000,"text":"that makes more energy than it needs to operate and purifies its own water."},{"time":927000,"text":"Here's a building for The Gap, where the ancient grasses"},{"time":929000,"text":"of San Bruno, California, are on the roof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"And this is our project for Ford Motor Company."},{"time":935000,"text":"It's the revitalization of the River Rouge in Dearborn."},{"time":937000,"text":"This is obviously a color photograph."},{"time":941000,"text":"These are our tools. These are how we sold it to Ford."},{"time":945000,"text":"We saved Ford 35 million dollars doing it this way, day one,"},{"time":948000,"text":"which is the equivalent of the Ford Taurus"},{"time":950000,"text":"at a four percent margin of an order for 900 million dollars worth of cars."},{"time":954000,"text":"Here it is. It's the world's largest green roof, 10 and a half acres."},{"time":957000,"text":"This is the roof, saving money,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and this is the first species to arrive here. These are killdeer."},{"time":964000,"text":"They showed up in five days."},{"time":967000,"text":"And we now have 350-pound auto workers"},{"time":969000,"text":"learning bird songs on the Internet."},{"time":973000,"text":"We're developing now protocols for cities --"},{"time":975000,"text":"that's the home of technical nutrients."},{"time":977000,"text":"The country -- the home of biological. And putting them together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980000,"text":"And so I will finish by showing you a new city"},{"time":982000,"text":"we're designing for the Chinese government."},{"time":984000,"text":"We're doing 12 cities for China right now,"},{"time":987000,"text":"based on cradle to cradle as templates."},{"time":989000,"text":"Our assignment is to develop protocols for the housing"},{"time":992000,"text":"for 400 million people in 12 years."},{"time":994000,"text":"We did a mass energy balance -- if they use brick,"},{"time":996000,"text":"they will lose all their soil and burn all their coal."},{"time":999000,"text":"They'll have cities with no energy and no food."},{"time":1001000,"text":"We signed a Memorandum of Understanding --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"here's Madam Deng Nan, Deng Xiaoping's daughter --"},{"time":1005000,"text":"for China to adopt cradle to cradle."},{"time":1007000,"text":"Because if they toxify themselves, being the lowest-cost producer,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"send it to the lowest-cost distribution -- Wal-Mart --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and then we send them all our money, what we'll discover is that"},{"time":1016000,"text":"we have what, effectively, when I was a student,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"was called mutually assured destruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"Now we do it by molecule. These are our cities."},{"time":1025000,"text":"We're building a new city next to this city; look at that landscape."},{"time":1028000,"text":"This is the site."},{"time":1030000,"text":"We don't normally do green fields, but this one is about to be built,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"so they brought us in to intercede."},{"time":1036000,"text":"This is their plan."},{"time":1038000,"text":"It's a rubber stamp grid that they laid right on that landscape."},{"time":1041000,"text":"And they brought us in and said, \"What would you do?\""},{"time":1044000,"text":"This is what they would end up with, which is another color photograph."},{"time":1048000,"text":"So this is the existing site, so this is what it looks like now,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"and here's our proposal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057000,"text":"So the way we approached this"},{"time":1059000,"text":"is we studied the hydrology very carefully."},{"time":1061000,"text":"We studied the biota, the ancient biota,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"the current farming and the protocols."},{"time":1065000,"text":"We studied the winds and the sun to make sure everybody in the city"},{"time":1067000,"text":"will have fresh air, fresh water and direct sunlight"},{"time":1073000,"text":"in every single apartment at some point during the day."},{"time":1076000,"text":"We then take the parks and lay them out as ecological infrastructure."},{"time":1080000,"text":"We lay out the building areas."},{"time":1083000,"text":"We start to integrate commercial and mixed use"},{"time":1084000,"text":"so the people all have centers and places to be."},{"time":1087000,"text":"The transportation is all very simple,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"everybody's within a five-minute walk of mobility."},{"time":1092000,"text":"We have a 24-hour street, so that there's always a place that's alive."},{"time":1097000,"text":"The waste systems all connect."},{"time":1099000,"text":"If you flush a toilet, your feces will go to the sewage treatment plants,"},{"time":1104000,"text":"which are sold as assets, not liabilities."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Because who wants the fertilizer factory that makes natural gas?"},{"time":1110000,"text":"The waters are all taken in to construct the wetlands for habitat restorations."},{"time":1115000,"text":"And then it makes natural gas, which then goes back into the city"},{"time":1119000,"text":"to power the fuel for the cooking for the city."},{"time":1123000,"text":"So this is -- these are fertilizer gas plants."},{"time":1125000,"text":"And then the compost is all taken back"},{"time":1128000,"text":"to the roofs of the city, where we've got farming,"},{"time":1130000,"text":"because what we've done is lifted up the city,"},{"time":1134000,"text":"the landscape, into the air to -- to restore the native landscape"},{"time":1141000,"text":"on the roofs of the buildings."},{"time":1143000,"text":"The solar power of all the factory centers"},{"time":1146000,"text":"and all the industrial zones with their light roofs powers the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1149000,"text":"And this is the concept for the top of the city."},{"time":1151000,"text":"We've lifted the earth up onto the roofs."},{"time":1155000,"text":"The farmers have little bridges to get from one roof to the next."},{"time":1159000,"text":"We inhabit the city with work/live space on all the ground floors."},{"time":1163000,"text":"And so this is the existing city, and this is the new city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}